To make forms we need 5 .py files
1. views.py
2.models.py
3.forms.py
4.admin.py
5.urls.py
These forms are of two types : 
a) Model forms (uses models.Model class in models.py page & forms.ModelForm class nforms.py)
b)Django Forms (uses forms.Form class in models.py page)

In django forms we do not need any models.py page but for higher authentication levels models.py forms are preffered (ref :  javapoint.com/django page)

MODEL FORMS

urls.py
from django.contrib import admin 
from django.urls import url
from app import views
urlpatterns = [
path('admin/',admin.site.urls)
path('page1/',views.function)
]

app/models.py
from django.db import models
class customer(models.Model):
name = models.CharField()
phone = models.CharFiels()
class Meta:
db_table = "student"
#the table is created in the default sqlite3 db under the student table

app/form.py
from app.models import customer
class cusform(forms.ModelForm):
class Meta:
model = customer
fields = "__all__"
#here customer class within models.py is saved in the model variable

app/views.py
from app/form import cusform
from django.shortcuts import render
def index(request):
a = cusform()
return render(request,'index.html',{'form':a})
#form.py imports from models.py and views.py import from form.py
index.html
<html>
<form method = "post">
{%csrf token}
{{form.as_p}}
</form>
</html>

DJANGO FORMS
Similar to model form except views.py imports directly from models.py

models.py
from django improt forms
class student(forms.Form):
name = forms.CharField()
phone = forms.CharField()

views.py
from app.models import student
from django.db import render
def index(request):
a = student()
return render(request , 'index.html' , {'form' : a})

index.html
<html>
<form method = "post">
{%csrd token}
{{form.as_p}}
</form>
</html>
